# State Management

{{#if (eq stateManagement "none")}}
- Prefer **local component state** and framework primitives (Context sparingly).
- Avoid prop drilling more than 2–3 levels — lift state or use composition.
{{/if}}

{{#if hasRedux}}
- Use **Redux Toolkit** slices; colocate slice + selectors; avoid large monolithic stores.
- Prefer RTK Query only if selected as data layer; otherwise keep queries separate.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasZustand}}
- One store per domain; export selectors; avoid storing non-serializable objects unless intentional.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasJotai}}
- Prefer atoms per concern; derive with `atom` + read-only dependencies.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasRecoil}}
- Avoid cross-atom cycles; document atom families for lists.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasPinia}}
- Setup stores with `defineStore`; prefer composition-style stores for complex domains.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasNgRx}}
- Actions/reducers/effects separated; selectors for derived data; keep facades thin.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasSvelteStores}}
- Use `writable` + `derived`; unsubscribe in `onDestroy` when subscribing manually.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasMobX}}
- Prefer `observer` boundaries; keep actions explicit; avoid mutating observables outside actions.
{{/if}}

## SSR / hydration

{{#if hasMetaFramework}}
- Ensure server and client render **consistent initial state**; avoid reading `window` during first paint on server bundles.
{{/if}}
